Public Health specialist, Andrew Robinson says the number of Covid-19 tests done doesn't reflect the true nature of the epidemic in South Africa. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Public Health specialist, Andrew Robinson says the number of COVID-19 tests conducted does not reflect the true nature of the epidemic in South Africa. According to Robinson, it is not known how the virus will interact with SA's HIV/Aids and Tuberculosis (TB) epidemics. "The true reality will only come once the data is in. So far, we are doing all we can with the resources that we have got." The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in SA is 3,034. Explainer: New amendments to the lockdown regulations Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize says over 100,000 tests have been conducted, mostly in the private sector. The death toll is now 52. Watch the full interview with Public Health specialist, Andrew Robinson in the video above. For an updated number of cases, click here. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.